# .templatesyncignore
#
# Files that must NOT be overwritten when syncing from the upstream
# ludeeus/integration_blueprint template. Uses .gitignore-style glob patterns.
#
# The upstream sync pulls with "-X theirs" (upstream wins on conflict), so this
# ignore list is the ONLY thing protecting your own code and identity. Keep it
# accurate. See the "Staying in sync with the blueprint" section of the README.

# --- Your integration code (never sync: it diverges the moment you build it) ---
custom_components/**

# --- Per-repo identity (yours, not the template's) ---
manifest.json
hacs.json
README.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
LICENSE
.devcontainer.json
config/configuration.yaml
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/**

# LICENSE is ignored for two reasons: it carries the upstream author's copyright
# line (yours to set), and upstream stores it with CRLF while .gitattributes
# normalizes to LF -- so syncing it produces a whole-file "every line changed"
# diff that is pure line-ending noise.

# Note: .templatesyncignore itself is never synced (the action restores it).
